{"type":"route","meta":{"status":200,"headers":{"content-type":"text/markdown","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/layout,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/[[...slug]]/route,_N_T_/llms.mdx/docs/commission/content.md"}},"body":"# Commission (/docs/commission)\n\n\n\nThe Commission page is where you define how much each staff member earns from the services they perform, and view a live breakdown of what they've earned. NxCut calculates everything automatically based on real sales data.\n\nClick **Commission** in the left menu to get started.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Commission is only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\nThe page is split into two sections: **Team Member Commissions** (your commission rules) and **Commission Calculations** (the live earnings breakdown).\n\n***\n\nTeam Member Commissions [#team-member-commissions]\n\nThis section lists all the commission rules you've set up. If no rules have been created yet, it will show \"No commission settings found — add a commission setting to get started.\"\n\n***\n\nSetting up a commission rule [#setting-up-a-commission-rule]\n\nClick **+ Add Commission** in the top right. A form will pop up.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Select a **Team Member** from the dropdown.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    The **Services Commission** section is enabled by default. This means the staff member earns commission on the services they perform.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Choose the **Default commission type**:\n\n    * **Fixed rate** — a set percentage applied to every sale they make\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Enter the **Default rate** — the percentage they'll earn (e.g., 30%).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set the **Sales period** — how often commission is calculated. The default is **Monthly**. NxCut will show you exactly when the first and following periods will be.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Use the **Sample calculation** box to double-check your setup. Enter a sale amount and NxCut will show you the exact commission calculation — including the threshold, commissionable amount, and final payout.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Create Commission** to save.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  The sample calculation updates in real time as you type — use it to make sure the numbers look right before saving.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nCommission Calculations [#commission-calculations]\n\nBelow the commission rules is the **Commission Calculations** table — a live breakdown of what each staff member has earned for the current period.\n\nAt the top you'll see four summary cards:\n\n| Card             | What it shows                             |\n| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |\n| Team Members     | Number of staff with sales in this period |\n| Total Sales      | Combined revenue across all staff         |\n| Total Commission | Total commission owed to the team         |\n| Avg Commission % | Average commission rate across the team   |\n\nThe table below shows each staff member with:\n\n* **Sales Count** — number of sales completed\n* **Total Sales** — their total revenue\n* **Commission Type** — their commission setup, or a **No Setup** badge if none has been configured\n* **Commission Rate** — their percentage\n* **Commission Amount** — what they've earned\n* **Actions** — an eye icon to view the breakdown, and a salary slip icon to open their slip\n\nClick **Export CSV** to download the full table for payroll processing.\n\n***\n\nSalary Slip [#salary-slip]\n\nClick the salary slip icon next to any team member to open their **Salary Slip**. This is a full payroll breakdown that can be filled in and downloaded.\n\nThe slip is headed with your salon's name and labelled as **Payroll Advice**. It shows the staff member's name, their occupancy percentage, free hours, the month, and their title.\n\n**Earnings section**\n\nA table where you can enter values for each earning type:\n\n| Earning      | Description                   |\n| ------------ | ----------------------------- |\n| Basic Salary | Their fixed monthly salary    |\n| Over Time    | Overtime hours worked         |\n| Voucher      | Commission from voucher sales |\n| Allowance    | Any allowances paid           |\n| Products     | Commission from product sales |\n| Bonus        | Any bonus payment             |\n| EOS          | End of service accrual        |\n| Target       | Target-based incentives       |\n\nEach row has editable fields for rate, days, and hours. The **Total Earning** is calculated automatically.\n\n**Deductions section**\n\nEnter any amounts to deduct:\n\n* Deduction\n* Cash advance\n* Additional deduction\n\nThe **Total Deduction** and final **Net Salary** are calculated automatically at the bottom.\n\nOnce the slip is complete, click **Download XLS** to save it as a spreadsheet, or **Close** to exit without saving.\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Feature            | Details                                                                             |\n| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Commission rules   | Set per staff member with a fixed rate and sales period                             |\n| Sample calculator  | Preview the commission payout before saving                                         |\n| No Setup badge     | Staff member has sales but no commission rule configured                            |\n| Calculations table | Live monthly breakdown per staff member                                             |\n| Export CSV         | Download the full calculations for payroll                                          |\n| Salary slip        | Full payroll advice with earnings, deductions, and net salary — downloadable as XLS |\n| Access             | Admin only                                                                          |\n"}